<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Why These Companies Work Better for Fast-Maturing Gardens</h2>

  <h3>They Offer Early Varieties Across Multiple Crops</h3>
  <p>
    A fast tomato does not solve the problem if your beans, cucumbers, and squash all take too long.
  </p>

  <p>
    Johnny’s and Territorial, in particular, tend to offer more early-maturing options across a wide range of vegetables, which makes it easier to build a consistently fast garden.
  </p>

  <h3>They Make Timing Easier to Compare</h3>
  <p>
    Fast gardening depends on comparing maturity timelines quickly and accurately.
  </p>

  <p>
    Strong seed companies make it easier to see which varieties are actually faster, rather than relying on vague labels like “early” or “quick.”
  </p>

  <h3>They Focus on Practical Performance</h3>
  <p>
    The best fast-maturing varieties are not just early on paper — they perform reliably under real conditions.
  </p>

  <p>
    Companies that serve market growers or serious home gardeners tend to select for this kind of consistency.
  </p>
