<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>The Problem with Most “Early” Varieties</h2>

  <p>
    Many gardeners assume that anything labeled “early” is fast enough. That is often not true.
  </p>

  <ul class="plainList">
    <li>“Early” is usually relative to other varieties, not your timeline.</li>
    <li>Some early crops are still too slow for short seasons or tight schedules.</li>
    <li>Different companies use the term differently.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This is why the overall catalog matters more than individual labels.
  </p>
</section>

